<p>'Congratulations, you've just blown up The Bachelorette,' Harrison tells her, as the promo comes to an end. </p>

<p>It was reported in August that Clare Crawley was replaced by Tayshia Adams, who appeared on Season 23 of The Bachelor, after Crawley fell for one of her original suitors while production was delayed due to COVID-19.</p>

<p>'One of her potential guys found a way to get in touch with her and they began talking,' a source told People in August. </p>

<p>Congrats: 'Congratulations, you've just blown up The Bachelorette,' Harrison tells her, as the promo comes to an end</p>

<p>'By the time filming officially began, they were basically already in love. No one else stood a chance. It just became so obvious from her subsequent few dates that her heart wasn’t in it and she just wasn’t feeling it. Then she said she wanted out,' the source added.</p>

<p>Production started last month at La Quinta Resort in Palm Springs, California last month, with Crawley spotted on the set, though it's not clear when Adams will begin her stint on the show.</p>

<p>A source added that, 'Tayshia was game and ready to go. What remains to be seen is if more men will be brought in now to give Tayshia a full roster of suitors.'</p>

<p>The Bachelorette wrapped filming last week, with the season premiere slated to air on Tuesday, October 13 on ABC. </p>

